39:02.680 --> 39:06.120
Do you always get up in the middle
of the night with Barbara?

39:06.120 --> 39:08.840
Usually.

39:08.840 --> 39:10.800
Wife's had her all day.

39:10.800 --> 39:14.800
So I thought I'd give
      Patti a little rest.

39:15.480 --> 39:19.480
Besides, gives me a little
more time with Barbara.

39:21.840 --> 39:24.680
There you go!

39:24.680 --> 39:27.240
OK. Would you heat up
a bottle out of the fridge?

39:27.240 --> 39:31.240
There's a pan of water
     over there on the stove.

39:38.240 --> 39:39.560
You don't want to boil it!

39:39.560 --> 39:43.560
You don't want to boil it!
No kidding.

39:53.320 --> 39:55.360
Let me ask you a question.

39:55.360 --> 39:58.440
How did you raise three kids
   in this sardine can?

39:58.440 --> 39:59.840
Well, we had a house.

39:59.840 --> 40:03.840
My father built it on a piece of
land. It's still up the road aways.

40:04.320 --> 40:06.960
A lot of love and care
went into that home.

40:06.960 --> 40:09.120
Why would you move?

40:09.120 --> 40:12.000
We sold it so the kids could go
 to a decent college.

40:12.000 --> 40:16.000
It's not right that they have
to start off life on their own
  with college loans.

40:18.400 --> 40:22.160
I tried to help my kids
   the way my father taught me.

40:22.160 --> 40:26.160
He came from Hungary in the early
1900s without a cent to his name.

40:26.160 --> 40:30.160
He was lucky he got a job
sorting mail on a train

40:31.080 --> 40:33.160
out of New York City to Buffalo.

40:33.160 --> 40:34.920
Ran right through Clinton here.

40:34.920 --> 40:37.680
It was dad's dream to buy
    a little piece of land,

40:37.680 --> 40:40.720
get us kids out of the city
   and up here.

40:40.720 --> 40:43.160
He wanted the best for his kids.

40:43.160 --> 40:46.040
And that's what I want for mine.

40:46.040 --> 40:48.320
